The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), will on Thursday visit Sokoto State to inaugurate BUA Cement’s three million metric tonnes per annum plant and 48 Megawatts power plant. He will also travel to Zamfara State to condole with the people over the recent attacks by bandits who have recently been declared as terrorists. This was disclosed by presidential aide, Buhari Sallau, in a post on his Facebook page. “President Muhammadu Buhari will be in Sokoto this morning, to commission #BUACement’s 3 million metric tonnes per annum Sokoto Plant and 48 Megawatts Power Plant, before proceeding to Zamfara to condole with the people over recent unfortunate attacks in parts of the state,” he wrote. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com